Having some trouble with LiveWindow; we threw our robot into Test Mode last night to spin motors, and Shuffleboard went into the continual connect/disconnect cycle. I restarted Shuffleboard with an empty layout, and the problem persisted. Our code has enableLiveWindowInTest(true);

The log shows a bunch of errors similar to:

Feb 21, 2024 7:30:37 PM edu.wpi.first.shuffleboard.app.json.WidgetSaver deserialize
WARNING: Saved source type is not present, adding destroyed source(s) instead
Feb 21, 2024 7:30:43 PM edu.wpi.first.shuffleboard.app.WidgetPaneController destroyedSourceCouldNotBeRestored
WARNING: Could not restore source: network_table:///LiveWindow/Ungrouped
...
Feb 21, 2024 7:30:43 PM edu.wpi.first.shuffleboard.app.WidgetPaneController destroyedSourceCouldNotBeRestored
WARNING: Could not restore source: network_table:///LiveWindow/Ungrouped/DutyCycle Encoder[4]/Is Connected
edu.wpi.first.shuffleboard.app.sources.DataTypeChangedException: The new data type is None, was expecting one of: [Boolean]
...
Feb 21, 2024 7:31:04 PM edu.wpi.first.shuffleboard.app.WidgetPaneController destroyedSourceCouldNotBeRestored
WARNING: Could not restore source: network_table:///LiveWindow/Ungrouped
edu.wpi.first.shuffleboard.app.sources.DataTypeChangedException: The new data type is Map, was expecting one of: [LW Subsystem]

Has anyone else seen this already? I don’t want to spend a lot of time gathering data on this if it’s a known problem.
